goals.question: What is the distribution of body mass across different penguin species?
goals.visualization: box plot of Body_Mass__g_ by Species
goals.rationale: This will help us understand if there are any significant differences in body mass between different penguin species.

goals.question: Is there a correlation between beak length and beak depth?

goals.rationale: This will help us understand if there is a relationship between the two variables and if they can be used interchangeably in analysis.

goals.question: What is the distribution of flipper length across different penguin species?

goals.rationale: This will help us understand if there are any significant differences in flipper length between different penguin species.

goals.question: What is the distribution of body mass by gender?

goals.question: What is the distribution of beak length across different islands?

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data.boxplot(column='Body_Mass__g_', by='Species')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of body mass across different penguin species?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.scatter(data['Beak_Length__mm_'], data['Beak_Depth__mm_'])
    ax.set_xlabel('Beak Length (mm)')
    ax.set_ylabel('Beak Depth (mm)')
    plt.title('Is there a correlation between beak length and beak depth?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna(subset=['Flipper_Length__mm_'])
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.boxplot([data[data['Species'] == 'Adelie']['Flipper_Length__mm_'], 
                data[data['Species'] == 'Chinstrap']['Flipper_Length__mm_'], 
                data[data['Species'] == 'Gentoo']['Flipper_Length__mm_']], 
               labels=['Adelie', 'Chinstrap', 'Gentoo'])
    ax.set_xlabel('Species')
    ax.set_ylabel('Flipper Length (mm)')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of flipper length across different penguin species?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna(subset=['Body_Mass__g_', 'Sex'])
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.boxplot([data[data['Sex'] == 'MALE']['Body_Mass__g_'], data[data['Sex'] == 'FEMALE']['Body_Mass__g_']])
    ax.set_xticklabels(['MALE', 'FEMALE'])
    ax.set_ylabel('Body Mass (g)')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of body mass by gender?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['Island', 'Beak_Length__mm_']]
    chart = data.boxplot(by='Island', figsize=(10,6))
    chart.set_xlabel('Island')
    chart.set_ylabel('Beak Length (mm)')
    chart.set_title('What is the distribution of beak length across different islands?')
    chart.axhline(y=data['Beak_Length__mm_'].median(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Median')
    chart.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
